data.description: This home and all of the surrounding homes were completely torn down in 2010/2011 and completely and beautifully rebuilt from the foundation up. The exterior of the home has been well maintained and has even added the quintessential American Dream white picket fence as a beautiful bow on top. Seller also added central air and a 160 sq ft shed out back. Once inside the home, on the first level you will find a nice open floor plan with charming kitchen with a 10 ft peninsula for added cabinetry and seating, a half bathroom and access to both the attached garage and partially finished basement. The hardwood floors still shine and are in great shape. Upstairs the home offers 4 great sized bedrooms and the full bathroom. In full disclosure the interior of the home does need some cosmetic TLC (mostly fixing sheetrock, adding a staircase balusters/handrails, upstairs carpet/flooring and some minor leaks in the bathroom). This home also offers a huge backyard and once the cosmetics have been attended to this home will once again sparkle and be the cutest home in the neighborhood.
